&gt; towards the exit

The other soldiers also follow suit, each taking a masking device.
Each mask was designed to mask the spark signature of each individual
it was attached to, making it difficult to scan for them.

The area around the shuttle was barren, very few trees and foliage,
and the ground was predominantly flat, it sloping up and down as one
walked or flew. Although the land was flat that did not mean it was
smooth, it was obvious to anyone looking that this area had been mined
long ago, and parts of it were still broken and choppy, the very dirt
still black and brown with mixtures of rust colored sediment.

Even the air itself was brown foggy haze, remenants of the smog that
seemed to live over the mining city roughly a mile away from here.

The soldiers each stood outside the shuttle, Inferno and Terrorsaur
standing near to Hydras like bodyguards, with Taratulus nearby like
some skulking meance. Injector, Buzzclaw, Terrorgator, and Quickstrike
also came out of the shuttle, each of them ready looking around an
eagerness to each step. Last came Waspinator, his optics quick and
furtive. Despite that he usually came back from battle in peices, he
seemed ready to back up his comrades, his weapon held firmly in hand.

&quot;This is all of us sir.&quot; Injector said, it seemed that for the moment
he had taken charge of the Fuzors in Skyshadow&#39;s absence, and he was
large and incharge. He smiled as he looked at Hydras, &quot;When ever you
are ready we will follow you.&quot;

